description:
R | 1h 36min | Biography, Drama, History

HBO biopic about the infamous "mad monk" Rasputin from the court of Tsar Nicholas in Russia. 


Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rasputin:_Dark_Servant_of_Destiny

Rasputin: Dark Servant of Destiny is a biographical 1996 TV film which chronicles the last four years (1912â€“16) of Grigori Rasputin's stint as a healer to Alexei Nikolaevich, Tsarevich of Russia; the heir apparent to the Russian throne as well as the only son of Tsar Nicholas II of Russia and Empress Alexandra Feodorovna; who suffered from hemophilia. The film is narrated in the first person by Alexei.

Rasputin: Dark Servant of Destiny won a Golden Globe for Best Mini-Series or Motion Picture made for TV.
Alan Rickman, starring as Rasputin, won an Emmy (along with Greta Scacchi playing Tsarina Alexandra) and a Golden Globe for his work in this movie.
Ian McKellen, playing Tsar Nicholas II, won a Golden Globe for Best Supporting Actor, and was nominated an Emmy for Best Supporting Actor.
